&lt;p&gt;This isn’t just an execution or admin role — it’s a leadership position for someone who can research, propose, and help drive future-focused IT strategies across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Achieve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and implement scalable, secure, AI-driven IT architectures aligned with business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research, propose, and implement AI/LLM-based automation for IT processes, support systems, and knowledge management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead AI initiatives and strategy sessions, chairing technology trend discussions and quarterly IT innovation reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and deploy cloud-native, automation-first IT systems — focused on resilience, performance, and zero-touch management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement AI-powered IT service desk solutions, compliance monitoring, incident response, and proactive issue resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide IT Operations in optimizing hardware lifecycle, SaaS platforms, and IT asset tracking through AI/automation-driven efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Security and Legal teams to align AI and IT architecture with compliance, risk management, and privacy standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive tool rationalization and consolidation projects using AI analytics to inform more intelligent decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering, AI/ML teams, and vendors to integrate IT systems into our broader AI development ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
