&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;Montserrat&#39;, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;Who we are&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;Montserrat&#39;, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; At Fortis Games we aspire to make great games that bring people together while redefining how game companies work. We believe in building a sense of belonging through our games, their communities, and how we operate and treat each other. Through our game communities, we will create powerful connections and lasting memories. We will foster a culture of diversity, equity and belonging where together our diverse skills, experiences and backgrounds impact the games we make. &lt;/span&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;Montserrat&#39;, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; We are an early but mighty organization with a leadership team of game industry veterans. There are many opportunities for you to have a big impact on the products we&#39;ll be making as well as the overall direction of the company. If you&#39;re passionate about tackling difficult problems with direct and thoughtful communication and team first mentality, we may be the right place for you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About the role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our ASO Specialist and owner of App Store Optimization across Fortis&#39;s portfolio for a 6-month contract term, you&#39;ll drive how our games show up across the App Store and Google Play, influencing everything from first impression to install. Working across titles in soft launch and global launch, you&#39;ll combine creativity, experimentation, player insight, and performance thinking to improve how players find, understand, and engage with our games.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on role with meaningful ownership from day one. You&#39;ll build and evolve experimentation frameworks, test new ideas, and partner closely with product, marketing, creative, and game teams to improve store performance across the portfolio — stepping in to run ASO execution while the Product Marketing team scales the function. From icons, screenshots, videos, and copy to keyword strategy and custom store experiences, you&#39;ll help shape the moments that connect players with our games.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who enjoys turning signals into action, challenges assumptions through testing, and can be effective from day one — this role needs minimal ramp-up given the contract term.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you&#39;ll achieve&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As ASO Specialist, you will own ASO execution across the Fortis portfolio for the contract term, including keyword strategy and metadata optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and run custom store experiences using Custom Product Pages (CPPs) and Custom Store Listings (CSLs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run A/B tests on store assets — icons, screenshots, video, copy — and translate results into next steps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve conversion rate across multiple titles simultaneously through structured experimentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate AI-driven workflows into ASO execution for keyword optimization, competitive analysis, and experimentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with UA, Creative, and Product Marketing to align store strategy with acquisition and positioning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect ASO decisions to broader growth strategy — not treat store performance as a standalone metric&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute from week one — minimal ramp-up expected given the contract term&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you&#39;ll need to be successful&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-platform ASO fluency across App Store and Google Play is essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience managing ASO for mobile apps or games, including CPPs and CSLs — non-negotiable&lt;/li

